definition.value: A class which contains food product categories qualified by a quality such as granularity or temperature, which is useful for tasks like food inspection where little prior knowledge of how the food came to be is available. Some terms like "food (frozen)" are both a quality descriptor and the output of a process.
A food product consisting of food material derived from ingredients sourced from multiple organisms.

The definition of this is being discussed in issue: https://github.com/FoodOntology/foodon/issues/57

Namely, how to characterize the threshold of ingredients that make for multi-component classification? Salt, pepper, spices wouldn't normally make a food multi-component?
A preserved food, where the moisture levels in the food product have been reduced to low levels to improve shelf life.
A food product organized by the process which it results from.
A lipid food product is a food product made primarily of plant or animal fat or oil
A whole dried bean is a bean resulting from natural or mechanical air drying applied to a bean or bean pod.
A seed of a bean plant from one of several genera of the flowering plant family (Fabaceae).
Cooked bean material is the bean material output of a cooking process applied to dry, rehydrated, or raw (fresh) beans.
A seed of a jack seed plant (Canavalia ensiformis).
A pigeon pea food product is a food product derived from the pigeon pea plant
A seed of a pigeon pea plant (Cajanus cajan).
A seed of a  velvet bean plant (Mucuna pruriens)
A seed of a vetch plant.
A liver food product is a food product that derives from one or more liver organs.
A genus of plants in the mustard family (Brassicaceae). The members of the genus are informally known as cruciferous vegetables, cabbages, or mustard plants.
A bean food product made from velvet bean.
A food product deriving from one or more animals.
